World Bank to Issue $1.2 Billion of Peru Loans, Spokeswoman Says

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-04-27T18:16:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/world-bank-to-issue-1-2-billion-of-peru-loans-spokeswoman-says.html
The  World Bank  will lend as much as
$1.2 billion to  Peru  over a period of about four years,
spokeswoman Sandra Arzubiaga said.  The loans will finance government agriculture, electricity,
water and sewerage projects, Arzubiaga said in a telephone
interview from  Lima  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  